I"½<p>Topic modeling is way of identifying patterns (topics) in a collection of documents.</p>

<p>This is only a proof of concept to check out the performance of the LDA algorithm at MLlib based on the posts:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://databricks.com/blog/2015/03/25/topic-modeling-with-lda-mllib-meets-graphx.html">Topic modeling with LDA: MLlib meets GraphX</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://databricks.com/blog/2015/09/22/large-scale-topic-modeling-improvements-to-lda-on-apache-spark.html">Large Scale Topic Modeling: Improvements to LDA on Apache Spark</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="data">Data</h2>

<p>The text used to this proof was extracted from the BBC Mundo web page using <a href="https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/bs4/doc/">Beautiful Soup</a>, a Python library for web scrapping. The code used is available in the <a href="https://github.com/juliettm/scrapy/blob/master/bbc_scraping.ipynb">BBC scraping</a> iPython notebook.</p>

<h2 id="proof-of-concept">Proof of concept</h2>

<p>Iâ€™ve use the <a href="https://zeppelin.apache.org/">Apache Zeppelin</a> environment to run the experimentation. This is a very useful tool that provides built-in <a href="http://spark.apache.org/">Apache Spark</a> integration.</p>

